Compiling C++ code using SWIG:

swig -c++ -python -o MeshProject_wrap.cpp MeshProject.i
gcc -fPIC $(python-config --includes) -c MeshProject_wrap.cpp MeshProject.cpp -I/usr/include/python
g++ -shared MeshProject_wrap.o MeshProject.o -o _MeshProject.so

Actually think that the one statement is unneccessary so try below:

swig -c++ -python -o sc_wrap.cpp sc.i
gcc -fPIC $(python-config --includes) -c sc_wrap.cpp sc.cpp
g++ -shared sc_wrap.o sc.o -o _sc.so


Explanations: 

MeshProject.i - Settings that define the swig compilation
              - Specify standard templates for input and output
              
MeshProject.cpp - Pretty much standard c++ class code. 
MeshProject.py - Automatically created. Provides the link between the two languages. 
